caption: Fantastic and flavorful food, I loved the character the spot has, and the workers were helpful. Will surely come back.
American food, my favorite treat. Don't worry if it's busy, it is worth the wait. Service is consistently great. It has a great interior. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I loved.

Pleasantly surprised by the quality of our meals. Stopped in for dinner the night before the Baltimore Marathon. The quesadilla was the best we have ever had. The Cobb Salad was very good, and the turkey wrap was excellent. They also have an excellent beer selection, and great happy hour specials. Sports bar in our hotel was a pleasant surprise. Good prices, good food, good service. Wings were tasty and steak salad was perfectly flavored.  Enthusiastically recommended!
Great chicken tacos and wonderful service. Recommend.

Pro:  The crab cake is good, but doesn't make a great sandwich.  Cons:  The waitress often disappeared, and did not check in with guest.  I order two items but only was charged for one and had to get it corrected.  The waitress had a small  Attitude when i ordered my drink (Maker Mark, one ice cube, and very little coke).

Super Duper has always been my favorite. There's something about the mix of meats and the cooking method that always respects and never overpowers the star of the show: the meat. Umami comes thorough, crusty exterior with medium interior, juicy, never overworked. 17 Light Restaurant
Wish they had more vegetarian options. We eat more than salad you know.

Crabcake sandwich had spoiled crabmeat. Took one bite and immediately knew it was not fresh. I should have been more careful ordering it out of season, however I didn't expect it to be spoiled. Brought it up to the server, he didn't ask if I wanted something else and still got charged for the full meal even though I didn't eat the sandwich. Pretty awful experience, left feeling scammed. Hopefully I don't get sick from the bite I took. Don't make the same mistake as me, go somewhere else.

I use to go here regularly when I worked downtown so recently went back.   Ordered the salad.  Forgot the name of it, but it has salsa n sour cream on the side.   It seemed like it was just ok compared to what I remember.   Chicken did not have a blackened flavor and I wouldn't get it again.   The servers were nice and attentive so that was good.  I remember this being a solid place overall so to be fair,  I didn't have enuf of a selection to rate other menu items.
Perfect location to meet a colleague for lunch.
Not a true fan. I had the quesadilla with steak. For 9 extra dollars there was HARDLY any steak on it. It was relatively clean. Located in a great area downtown though.
It was pretty good
Service was very slow, food was over priced and just okay
Good place to go for lunch lots of sandwich options would go back again
First time visiting. The place is beautiful and my food was delicious.
The bar was great
Delicious, juicy burger...the Bang Bang Shrimp was perfect...and extremely friendly wait staff.

This place is a hidden jem!! Never a wait, excellent food and great service. We've eaten at almost every restaurant in the harbor (even the most expensive ones) and the chefs here are very talented. We visit Baltimore 2-3 times a year and this is my favorite place to eat. You will not be disappointed:)
No good selection of food and security flirts with all the women that work there

I do not recommend it.  Very slow, messed up bill twice and food was just ok.  It is easy if you are staying at the hotel but you may want to find other options, we wished we did.  It has a lot of potential though.
This place is amazing! Everything I have ever ordered has been delicious. Food is great, atmosphere is very friendly.

I sat at the bar, the bartender was friendly but very slow. I ordered the special, steak tacos with peppers and onions...not overly impressed. I got buffalo wings for a starter that they were ok. I got a slice of cheesecake to go, and tried to eat it when I got back to my room and it was frozen solid - literally solid. The total bill was $48 before tip....spend your money somewhere else.
The place is very nice and the service was good but It took over an hour for us to get our food. My steak came out overcooked, and the appetizers took over 40 minutes. Will not return!

Waited for over and hour and half for food.  Apparently this was because we ordered steaks medium well. Which wasn’t the case only 1 was medium well the other was medium rare.  Food came out and definitely did not take an hour and a half to cook. The Cajun steak had no Cajun seasoning on it and no spice or heat. We were eating at 230 in he afternoon too. Was not Bush. Overall avoid it.
Not a good one ..... I had the tuna and it was bad. Also... this is a caesar salad? Come on... get it together.
Ahi Tuna Tacos were very good!

There was no one to seat us,table wasn't clean,neither was the floor or booth, one waitress working, and food was slow. The waitress was very nice but it was dead and dry in there. Food wasn't bad just needed more flavor and the tea was lacking sugar lol.
I tried the special of the day which was the jerk chicken sandwich with pineapple slaw. I did not like it at all. The fries we're good though.

17 Light is a cool little bar restaurant with a nice vibe. The Tuna app and loaded tots were excellent. The burgers were superb as well. The cocktail and wine selections offer an array of choices to choose from. It's located only 2 blocks away from the Inner Harbor-The Charm'tastic Mile.

Out of everything we ordered no discount for this either. Frier broken. Food took entirely too long for what was ordered. Quality poor. Way overpriced for what is offered. If being under construction is affecting the menu this poorly might as well shut down.
Nice looking place. Food was pretty good
Great place to eat

If you want a quick tasty bite, this place provides several good options. The steak salad, crab cakes, and Reuben sandwich are all good choices. My burger came undercooked, so order medium well done. The white chocolate raspberry cheesecake is delicious. Room service at the Residence Inn is very convenient when you are not in the mood for the restaurant scene.

Quite busy, but the food was great and so was the service.

Great menu options (unique burgers and salads) and specials (1/2 price burgers).  Friendly staff.
Good food

The atmosphere is great - it's very clean and updated and overall really nice. I got the loaded tots with tiger sauce - which were also good in the moment, just a little greasy - however, that same night and the entire day after and counting I became so ill. I would certainly not go here again. They have a bar and everything so you would think it would be busy on a Saturday night - but it wasn't, AT ALL. There must be a reason! Overall I would not recommend the loaded tots at the least, but I get a feeling the tots aren't the only reason people aren't coming here...
Great service with a fun bartender.
Caesar salad, best ever. Ordered the crab ravioli, best I have ever had. The service was great, Cat, was attentive and helpful. I will definitely be back.
Good business casual meeting place and a variety of food options.
Great weekly specials
Quick and easy eats, whether you're staying nearby or a local. Good beers on tap, small cozy bar area, and normal seating.
The worst! When you ask you for a glass of sangria and and hour later you're like really never mind:/
Wow, this place was a new low in both food and service.

Just ate there yesterday. The bar staff (bartender/waitress) was not very friendly. It seemed like they were doing us a favor by serving us. No smiles, No greeting, and No kids' menus. The menu they do have though, makes your mouth water. So we ordered food to-go hoping it was better than the staff, but was a little disappointed. We ordered the Chicken Parm and their signature Pit Beef sandwiches, both avg at best. We specifically asked the Bartender whether the Jalapenos Bacon Mac&Cheese was pre-mixed with Jalapenos. His answer was NO, so we ordered a bacon Mac&Cheese with NO Jalapenos for my 2 year old. Opening it up in our hotel room, we realized that they gave us Jalapenos in the Mac&Cheese and No Bacon. REALLY!!!!?? We went back to return it to get a refund, but they could not even do that right!  There was no manager or authority on duty, so we weren't able to get a refund on the card right away. The bartender offered to replace the order, but since the original order took 25 minutes, we did not try to re-order anything.  The staff could care less! Their solution was "come back tomorrow". WHAT A JOKE!!
Thank you for taking care of myself and Family, Saturday Night services fantastic.
